definitions.definition: A member of a Christian religious community of women who live by certain vows and usually wear a habit , ( Roman Catholicism , specifically ) those living together in a cloister .
( by extension ) A member of a similar female community in other confessions .
A kind of pigeon with the feathers on its head like the hood of a nun.

definitions.definition: The fourteenth letter of many Semitic alphabets or abjads ( Phoenician , Aramaic , Hebrew , Syriac , Arabic and others).
